title: $A, $US fall in overnight trade
text:
Fri, Jul 24, 2015, 7:16 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 2 hrs 44 mins $A, $US fall in overnight trade AAP â€“ 31 minutes ago Print 
The Australian dollar is lower against the greenback which also fell overnight despite the release of upbeat US economic data. 
At 0630 AEST on Friday, the local currency was trading at 73.53 US cents, down from 73.68 cents on Thursday. 
The Aussie initially bounced in the overnight session to 74.17 US cents but later slid to 73.57 US cents, before easing further on Friday morning. 
The US dollar also slipped even though US jobless claims fell by 255,000 more than economists expected. 
CURRENCY SNAPSHOT AT 0630 AEST ON FRIDAY 
One Australian dollar buys: 
* 73.53 US cents, from 73.68 cents on Thursday 
* 91.10 Japanese yen, from 91.36 yen 
* 66.90 euro cents, from 67.39 euro cents 
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session) 
Source: IRESS Terms
